repository-code: >-
  https://github.com/alejandroromeroprieto/anaesthetic-project.git
abstract: >-
  The environmental impact of anaesthetic agents has been
  evaluated almost exclusively through global warming
  potential (GWP) and CO2-equivalent metrics. These
  frameworks have been criticised for failing to capture the
  dynamic response of the climate system to short-lived
  climate forcers like volatile anaesthetics and may provide
  a misleading basis for clinical guidelines and healthcare
  policy. We aimed to quantify the actual global mean
  surface temperature effect of general anaesthesia using a
  physically-based reduced-complexity climate model, and to
  compare the temperature trajectories of different
  anaesthetic strategies under different policy scenarios. 
